page.title: 03The land behind Carlingwark
page.content: The land behind Carlingwark House is made up of marsh and bog holes. Round about Carlingwark are a lot of little streams running through. There is a wood next to one of the fields. There is a stream that looks like the letter T. Many have fences beside them, which you have to climb to get over when you want to cross the water. There is a lot of long grass and a few trees in the fields. Most of them are crooked with branches sticking out over the place. There are very few hills but most are flat with bumps. The streams have a few stones and old bits of twigs in them.
